    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate for LawDog centers on two high-upside plays in the outfield: **Daulton Varsho** (69.94) and **Tyler Freeman** (69.01). **Daulton Varsho** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Woods Richardson, with his score buoyed by a +19% SP skill advantage and a strong platoon edge. Meanwhile, **Tyler Freeman** thrives in a hitter-friendly park (+14% adjustment), making him a premium play despite the neutral platoon stance. These two, alongside **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (69.82)\u2014who anchors the lineup pending his official #3 spot\u2014represent our elite tier of daily efficiency. The inclusion of **Bryson Stott** (60.16) is a tactical nod to his high SB ceiling, as his matchup against P\u00e9rez provides a +4% boost for a \"Slow SP Delivery\" environment that we are aggressively targeting to bolster our scarcest category.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was undoubtedly **Cal Raleigh** (50.44), who fell just shy of the starting threshold. While **Cal Raleigh** possesses a high base projection, the matchup against Ragans\u2019 3.07 xERA\u2014combined with a park penalty\u2014eroded his efficiency compared to the specific platoon and order advantages held by **Yainer Diaz** and **Will Smith**. Elsewhere, we remain cautious regarding the trio of **Luis Arraez**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Matt Chapman** against the elite arm of McClanahan. Their scores are suppressed by the negative park factors and the skill of the opposing starter, though their participation remains necessary given our roster depth constraints. Monitor the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, as any shift from the #3 hole would necessitate a recalculation of his daily floor, though his raw talent makes him a locked-in start regardless of situational variance.",
